{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"673732b0-b6cc-4bbf-b713-9b4358771706","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JyWp5p18YaGmtQzJtv3r6j","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Configuring NativeAOT crash dumps"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"b40a3309-0385-41e2-aa08-740a7443ee09","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. For .NET NativeAOT crash dumps, you need to set specific environment variables\n2. The key environment variables for crash dump collection with `createdump` are:\n   - `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables automatic crash dump generation\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - sets the dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - sets the dump file path/name pattern\n   - `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` - enables diagnostics for createdump itself\n   - `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` - points to the createdump tool location since NativeAOT doesn't bundle it\n\nFor NativeAOT in .NET 8+, these use the `DOTNET_` prefix rather than `COMPlus_`. In Kubernetes, I need to consider where crash dumps get written and how to persist them, likely through a volume mount so they survive pod restarts.","outputTokens":442,"requestId":"980F:3387D:541D275:5CAF128:69F406AF"},"id":"55a0c845-6bed-43da-ada3-5f62c26c8c6b","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:49:45.217Z","parentId":"fca120b6-4af8-48fd-81d6-b12a1d8e577f"}
